 look. They aren't absolutely horrible, but they're pretty gross. Here's what you need to get yourself. So you want pine salt. It has to be the original scent, guys. The other stuff doesn't work, okay? It has to be this original scent because this is the scent that the bugs and the animals hate. Then get a spray bottle. We're going to use the pour-in method, and we're going to use this to finish it off. Okay, so this is a healthy bag, so when we do diaper genies, which is what people call this, what we do is we fill them up in the bathtub all the way to the top with a couple glugs of bleach and let them soak for a few hours. Just to get the smell out, and then after that, we just take them outside and let them dry in the sun. The UV rays from the sun help kill any mold or any inside of it. Kind of like sanitizes it. They actually waste so much water. If you want to scrape stuff off the bottom without crawling in there, I just use like a broiler. Look at how good they look. So much better. Okay, now the whole point of this story. So take the pine salt, once they're all cleaned, and just spray them. You can spray the outsides of them too, you guys. And this is going to keep the bugs and animals away. And we just let it dry. That's it. And you can like, I just hang it here and then do it like once a week. Another trick we do is a bungee cord just on the front bar. And then we just hook it on and attach it to this. It keeps the animals away and stops the lids blowing off or whatever. So, the end.", "history": [{"date": "2026-07-18", "plays": 463152, "likes": 6757, "comments": 113}], "still_climbing": false, "hook_type": "Scenario/Hypothetical"}, {"shortCode": "DavT9LTOvbG", "url": "https://www.instagram.com/p/DavT9LTOvbG/", "caption": "Monday morning \u2615\ufe0f anyone?", "timestamp": "2026-07-13T16:14:19.000Z", "videoDuration": 11.352, "videoPlayCount": 500187, "videoViewCount": null, "likesCount": 2279, "commentsCount": 101, "displayUrl": "https://scontent-mia3-2.cdn